# Contributing Guide

## License & Copyright
All code contributions to this project are subject to a Contributor License Agreement (CLA).
By submitting a Pull Request, you agree to sign the CLA located at `docs/legal/CLA.md`.

What the CLA means:
1. You confirm your contribution is original, no copyright infringement.
2. You grant the project owner perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, transferable rights to use, modify, distribute, sublicense your code, including both open-source AGPLv3 use and commercial licensing sales.
3. You still retain personal copyright of your own contributed code.

Pull requests will not be merged until CLA signature is completed.
